word_mean_info__list.difference: 侧重到达目的地或达到某一目标。也可用作比喻。
既可指到达目的地，又可指到达途中的中间站。强调经过的周折或付出的努力。
普通用词，含义广泛。强调到达的动作或进程，不侧重是否到达目的地。也可用于比喻意义。
侧重指变得与原来截然不同，有时含贬义。
常指某人或某物有意无意地获得引起变化的因素，结果使变成另一状态。
常指逐渐地变成新状态，强调渐变的过程。
最普通用词，作为连系动词，指从一个状态向另一个状态的变化。
侧重变化的经过或过程，多用于不良情况。
作为连系动词，通常与形容词连用，指进入某种状态，从而发生变化，多指不好的状态。

list.abstract: come（英[kʌm]，美[kʌm]），英语单词，作动词为来；进入；发生。作介词为当（时间）来临；当…发生。作名词为性交高潮时射出的精液。短语搭配有come up with（提出，想出）。例句为“The ubiquitous battery has already come a long way, of course.（毋庸置疑，无处不在的电池经历了漫长的发展过程。）” come相关近义词有occur、happen等，相关反义词有go、leave。
《come》是法兰西女歌手Jain发行的第一首歌，收录在个人首张EP 《Hope》里，同时收录在专辑内的还有歌曲“Hope”“City”及“Makeba”。

yingyinNormal.en: When they come, and they will, they'll come for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们来的时候，他们肯定会来，会来找你算账。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, here. Come on, come on. Keep up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 来，快点，跟上。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, then come or don't. I don't care.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你们爱来不来，我无所谓。

yingyinNormal.en: No, come on. Let me show you around. Come on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，来吧，我带你到处看看。来把！

yingyinNormal.en: Cool. Yeah. Come on Ben.
yingyinNormal.zh: 酷。来，班。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on. Let's play. Yes, let's play.
yingyinNormal.zh: 来吧！我们来玩吧！好的，我们来玩吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Olaf! Come on. I'm coming!
yingyinNormal.zh: 雪宝! 来吧 我来了！

yingyinNormal.en: You have come from Lake-town.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是从长湖城来的。

yingyinNormal.en: Ready or not, here I come.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你藏好了吗，我要来找你啦。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe you could come with me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许..你可以跟我来。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on home before the storm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 暴风雨要来了快回基地。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on. Try it. It's natural.
yingyinNormal.zh: 来嘛，尝一尝。很自然。

yingyinNormal.en: She knew I'd come for her. Yes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她知道我会来找她的。不错。

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose you know why I've come.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道我为什么来这儿吗。

yingyinNormal.en: Suzy Sheep has come to play with Peppa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 苏西来找佩奇玩。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. I made my wife come down, too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我还让我老婆一起来了呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Children, come downstairs right now. Mummy. We're coming.
yingyinNormal.zh: 孩子们，你们现在都快下楼来。妈妈，我们来啦。

yingyinNormal.en: Did she ask you to come here and do this?
yingyinNormal.zh: 是她让他来的吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa and George have come to play again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩佩和乔治又来玩了。

yingyinNormal.en: Billy. Where the hell you been? Come on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 比利。你去哪了？快来。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: "When I <highlight>come</highlight> home from a hard day's work, I often feel tired," Danaher says.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 丹纳赫说: “当我辛苦工作一天回到家时，我经常感到疲惫。”

examination_example.sentence: These travelers to North America <highlight>came</highlight> in small, unmercifully overcrowded craft.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些前往北美的移民们乘坐拥挤的小船漂洋过海而来。

examination_example.sentence: The danger will <highlight>come</highlight> with Charles, who has both an expensive taste of lifestyle and a pretty hierarchical view of the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 保持奢侈的生活品味和奉行的等级森严的世界观的查尔斯将陷入危险的境地。

examination_example.sentence: The finding shows how sensitive rats are to social cues, even when they <highlight>come</highlight> from basic robots.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这一发现表明，即使是来自基本机器人的社交线索，老鼠也非常敏感。

examination_example.sentence: Most of the money would <highlight>come</highlight> from a penny-per-letter permanent rate increase and from shifting postal retirees into Medicare.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大部分资金将来自每封信一便士的永久费率提高，以及将邮政退休人员转移到医疗保险后留出的部分资金。

examination_example.sentence: Astronomy and Hawaiian culture both seek to answer big questions about who we are, where we <highlight>come</highlight> from and where we are going.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 天文学和夏威夷文化都试图回答关于我们是谁、我们来自哪里和我们要去哪里的重大问题。

examination_example.sentence: When it <highlight>came</highlight> to photographic portraits there could be "nothing more damning than a silly, foolish smile fixed forever".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当涉及到摄影肖像时，“没有什么比一个愚蠢的、永远不变的微笑更可恶的了”。

examination_example.sentence: The well-structured daily plans would be most effective when it <highlight>came</highlight> to the execution of tasks.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当涉及到执行任务时，规划很好的日常计划是最有效的。

examination_example.sentence: Gap year experiences can lessen the blow when it <highlight>comes</highlight> to adjusting to college.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在涉及到适应大学时，间隔年的经历可以减缓冲击。

examination_example.sentence: Second, it is surely a good thing that the money and attention <highlight>come</highlight> to science rather than go elsewhere.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 第二，资金和注意力投向科学而不是其他地方，这无疑是一件好事。

examination_example.sentence: Indeed, predictions have been around for two decades but have not yet <highlight>come</highlight> to fruition.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，预言已经存在了20年，但还没有实现。

examination_example.sentence: It was not until the mid-1980s that pink fully <highlight>came</highlight> into its own, when it began to seem inherently attractive to girls.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到20世纪80年代中期，粉色才开始崭露头角，开始对女孩具有与生俱来的吸引力。

sense_info_list.zh: 发生; 出现; 体现

examination_example.sentence: While climate is a key element, Moritz says, it shouldn't <highlight>come</highlight> at the expense of the rest of the equation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Moritz说到，虽然气候是一个关键因素，但它不应该牺牲同等重要的因素为代价。

examination_example.sentence: Popularity usually <highlight>comes</highlight> after quality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 受欢迎程度通常排在质量之后。

examination_example.sentence: But the real gains <highlight>come</highlight> in benefits and work practices.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但真正的收益来自于福利与工作事务。

examination_example.sentence: Only recently have they <highlight>come</highlight> to see the vital part forests will have to play in storing carbon.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到最近，他们才明白森林在储存碳方面所起的重要作用。

examination_example.sentence: As you will <highlight>come</highlight> to see, knowing that mental health is always available.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你会慢慢发现，明白心理健康一直在身边。

examination_example.sentence: When we <highlight>come</highlight> to think back on it, we can't remember the journey well because we didn't pay much attention to it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们回想起这段旅程时，我们记不太清楚了，因为我们没有太注意它。

examination_example.sentence: Arizona police would be allowed to verify the legal status of people who <highlight>come</highlight> in contact with law enforcement.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 亚利桑那州警方将被允许核实与执法部门接触的人的法律地位。

examination_example.sentence: You are the lucky inheritor of a dream <highlight>come</highlight> true.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你是梦想成真的幸运继承者。

examination_example.sentence: You also quickly learn to adapt and <highlight>come</highlight> up with creative solutions to the problems the painting presents.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你也很快学会适应，并想出创造性的解决方案来解决绘画中出现的问题。

examination_example.sentence: Mental health is the source of creativity for <highlight>coming</highlight> up with a creative business idea or invention to make our lives easier.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 心理健康是创造力的源泉，它能让我们想出一个有创意的商业想法或发明，让我们的生活更轻松。

examination_example.sentence: It hurts their economies, depriving them of much-needed skilled workers who could have <highlight>come</highlight> up with new products for their factories to make.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这损害了他们的经济，剥夺了他们急需的技术工人，而这些工人本可以为他们的工厂生产新产品。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Comes</highlight> across as reliable evidence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为可靠的证据突然出现。

examination_example.sentence: Professor Balch points out that fire is something man should <highlight>come</highlight> to terms with.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 鲍尔奇教授指出，人和火应该和谐相处。

examination_example.sentence: You wanted to say something — the first word — but it just won't <highlight>come</highlight> out, it feels like it is stuck somewhere.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你想说些什么——第一个词——但它就是说不出来，感觉像是卡在什么地方了。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Come</highlight> on — Everybody's doing it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 来吧——每个人都在这么做。

examination_example.sentence: However, their campaign risks <highlight>coming</highlight> a cross as being pushy and overprotective.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，他们的宣传运动可能会给人一种强势和保护过度的感觉。

examination_example.sentence: But most people will <highlight>come</highlight> away from this book believing it was money well spent.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但大多数人读完这本书后会认为物有所值。

examination_example.sentence: This is where supermarkets and their anonymity <highlight>come</highlight> in handy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这就是超市及其匿名性派上用场的地方。

examination_example.sentence: People who perceived greater social support were less likely to <highlight>come</highlight> down with a cold.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那些感觉得到更多社会支持的人患感冒的可能性较小。

word_usage.usage:
come+to do不定式用于疑问句，表示怎么或为什么；用在陈述句中，多指“达到（认识、例句或相信的程度）”
权威例句：How do you come to be so late?你怎么这么晚？
She had come to see the problem in a new light.她开始用新的角度来看待这个问题。

examination_example.sentence: A hurricane was <highlight>coming</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 飓风即将来临。

examination_example.sentence: You can't see it, smell it, or hear it, and people disagree on how precisely to define it, or where exactly it <highlight>comes</highlight> from.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你看不见它，闻不到它，听不到它，人们对如何准确定义它，或者它的确切来源存在分歧。

examination_example.sentence: Census data has shown Australians <highlight>come</highlight> from more than 200 countries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人口普查数据显示，澳大利亚人口来自200多个国家。

examination_example.sentence: After the time of testing <highlight>comes</highlight> a time of reflection and then of action.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在测试时间之后是反思时间，然后是行动时间。

examination_example.sentence: Other transport must <highlight>come</highlight> under far greater scrutiny.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他交通工具造成的环境损害必须受到更严格的审查。

examination_example.sentence: The problem <highlight>comes</highlight> when everyone is using a navigation app which tells them to avoid everyone else using the same gadget.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当每个人都在使用导航应用程序时，问题就来了，该应用程序告诉他们不要让其他人使用相同的设备。

examination_example.sentence: Today's battery breakthroughs <highlight>come</highlight> as the world looks to expand modern energy access to the billion or so people without it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今，电池技术的突破正值世界寻求将现代能源扩展到大约10亿没有现代能源的人。

examination_example.sentence: Oil <highlight>comes</highlight> from Trinidad, Aruba and Curacao.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 石油来自特立尼达、阿鲁巴和库拉索岛。

examination_example.sentence: The world's best rum <highlight>comes</highlight> from this area.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 世界上最好的朗姆酒来自这个地区。

examination_example.sentence: Where successful people's strengths <highlight>come</highlight> from.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 成功人士的优势从何而来。

examination_example.sentence: To my way of thinking, there are two main potential benefits that <highlight>come</highlight> from unleashing an agitated stream of truth during an exit interview.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在我看来，在离职面试中释放激动人心的真相有两个主要的潜在好处。

examination_example.sentence: Working for a new venture <highlight>comes</highlight> with a lot of risks—that is, instability, unclear responsibilities and the need to be a master of all trades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为一个新的企业工作伴随着很多风险——不稳定，责任不明确，需要精通所有的行业。

examination_example.sentence: There are some who say Marconi lost his edge when commercial broadcasting <highlight>came</highlight> along.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有人说，当商业广播出现时，Marconi就失去了他的优势。

examination_example.sentence: They saved the main structure, but it all <highlight>came</highlight> down to 15-30 minutes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们保住了主体结构，但最后只剩下15-30分钟。

examination_example.sentence: When it <highlight>comes</highlight> to changing people's minds, it is very difficult to jump from one side to another.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当涉及到改变人们的想法时，从一个方面跳到另一个方面是非常困难的。

examination_example.sentence: When it <highlight>comes</highlight> to transfer effects of music, scientists frequently point to brain plasticity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当谈到音乐的传递效应时，科学家们经常指出大脑的可塑性。

examination_example.sentence: It's clear that food manufacturers must tread carefully when it <highlight>comes</highlight> to using absence claims.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 很明显，食品制造商在使用缺货声明时必须小心谨慎。

examination_example.sentence: A study has found that educational TV shows <highlight>come</highlight> with an added lesson that influences the child's behavior.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一项研究发现，教育电视节目带有影响孩子行为的附加课程。

examination_example.sentence: From the West Indies also <highlight>come</highlight> oil, mineral pitch and many forest products.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 西印度群岛地区还生产石油、柏油和许多林产品。

examination_example.sentence: The news has left investors and consumers outraged but <highlight>comes</highlight> as little surprise to those in the fashion industry.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这一消息让投资者和消费者感到愤怒，但对时装业的人来说并不意外。

examination_example.sentence: This may <highlight>come</highlight> as a surprise to some.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这可能会让一些人感到惊讶。

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>came</highlight> together at the first Global Conference on Agricultural Research to begin working out how to change research agendas.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们在第一届全球农业研究会议上聚在一起，开始研究如何改变研究议程。

examination_example.sentence: How <highlight>come</highlight> the UK has been slow in imposing the tourist tax?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为什么英国迟迟不征收旅游税？

word_usage.usage: come+静态动词的不定式，构成复合谓语，表示一种情况变化的过程，如由“不知”到“知之”，?由“不理解”到“理解”。如：他逐渐认识到科学的重要性。He came to realize the importance of studying science.
come across表示“遇见”，后可直接跟宾语，不需加介词。

come near后接动名词形式，表示“几乎到…的程度”，come near to表示“接近…”。
他差点被射死。
误 He came very near to be shot.
正 He came very near being shot.

come为非延续性动词，不与表示一段时间的状语连用。have come（已经来），表示一个单程，即“人现在还在这儿，没有离开”。
他到我这儿来过三次了。
误 He has come here three times.
正 He has been here three times.

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 普通用词, 含义广泛。强调到达的动作或进程, 不侧重是否到达目的地。也可用于比喻意义。
不及物动词后接 to, get to Beijing。
最普通用词, 作为连系动词, 指从一个状态向另一个状态的变化。
侧重变化的经过或过程, 多用于不良情况。
常指逐渐地变成新状态, 强调渐变的过程。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

examination_example.sentence: I heard he comes here a lot, so I thought I'd <highlight>come</highlight> in and check with you.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我听说他经常来这里，所以我想我应该进来问问你。

examination_example.sentence: Five- to nine-year-olds <highlight>come</highlight> to the hospital with something in their ears the most.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 五到九岁的孩子来医院时耳朵里东西最多。

examination_example.sentence: Each Friday night a truck <highlight>came</highlight>, with cases of food that had to be unloaded, priced, and placed on shelves.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每周五晚上都会有一辆卡车来，装载着需要卸货、定价和上架的食品。

examination_example.sentence: And that disruption is surely <highlight>coming</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种颠覆肯定会发生。

examination_example.sentence: What we know from research is that from grateful people <highlight>come</highlight> good things.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们从研究中得知，心怀感激的人会给别人带来美好。

examination_example.sentence: This increase of digital use <highlight>comes</highlight> with rising risks of obesity, sleep deprivation and cognitive (认知的) , language and social- emotional delays.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 数字使用的增加伴随着肥胖、睡眠不足以及认知、语言和社会情感延迟风险的增加。

examination_example.sentence: Human brains <highlight>come</highlight> equipped with certain quantitative instincts that are refined with age, but these instincts are very limited.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人类的大脑具有一定数量的随着年龄增长而完善的本能，但这些本能是很有限的。

examination_example.sentence: With time, they start to understand that a given number represents a quantity greater by one than the number <highlight>coming</highlight> before it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着时间的推移，他们开始明白一个给定的数字代表一个比它前面的数字大一的量。

examination_example.sentence: Service stations <highlight>came</highlight> with the motorway and the legend of the transport cafe was born.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 服务站随高速公路而来，交通咖啡馆的传奇由此诞生。

examination_example.sentence: What have businesses <highlight>come</highlight> to recognize now?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 企业现在意识到了什么？

examination_example.sentence: The regulation will <highlight>come</highlight> into full effect next month.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项规定将于下月全面生效。

examination_example.sentence: The author has <highlight>come</highlight> to agree that food shortages could ultimately lead to the collapse of world civilization.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作者认同食物短缺最终会导致世界文明的崩溃。

examination_example.sentence: Park the car on those huge supermarket car parks then not be able to find it again after you <highlight>come</highlight> out of the shops.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 把车停在巨大的超市停车场，而你购物完出来后就找不到你的车了。

examination_example.sentence: What family background people <highlight>come</highlight> from.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们的家庭背景都是怎样的?

examination_example.sentence: Most of us volunteers breathe a sigh of relief when the season <highlight>comes</highlight> to a close.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当节日临近尾声时，我们大多数志愿者都会松一口气。

examination_example.sentence: When people try to interrupt you, let them know to <highlight>come</highlight> back during that time or that you'll find them then.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 别人想干扰你时，让他们知道要在这段时间内回来找你，否则你会去找他们。

examination_example.sentence: The weatherman said the sun wouldn't <highlight>come</highlight> out until next week.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 天气预报员说下星期才出太阳。

examination_example.sentence: Middle-aged homemakers, retirees, and the unemployed <highlight>come</highlight> to such cafes to talk about love, anger, and dreams with a psychologist.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中年家庭主妇、退休人员和失业人员来到这样的咖啡馆与心理学家谈论爱情、愤怒和梦想。

examination_example.sentence: Its old skin <highlight>came</highlight> off.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它的旧皮脱落了。

examination_example.sentence: When the chance <highlight>came</highlight> for a weekend to Sarasota, Florida, my bags were packed before you could say "sunshine".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当周末去佛罗里达萨拉索塔度假的机会来临时，我还没来得及说“阳光”就打包好了行李。

examination_example.sentence: Just at that time, the traveler who made the payment <highlight>came</highlight> downstairs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 就在那时，付钱的旅客下楼了。

examination_example.sentence: Then the door banged (砰地一声) open as the children <highlight>came</highlight> home from school.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子从学校到家时，门砰地一声开了。

examination_example.sentence: The summer holiday was <highlight>coming</highlight> but Zach was a little sad.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 暑假快到了,但扎克有点难过。

examination_example.sentence: Just as they were <highlight>coming</highlight> to blows, a lion happened to pass.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 就在它们两快要打起来时，一头大象碰巧经过。

examination_example.sentence: If you blow all of it off in one breath, your wish will <highlight>come</highlight> true!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你一口气把它吹灭，你的愿望就会实现！

examination_example.sentence: Though their school might not be modern, their dream of having a school near their homes has <highlight>come</highlight> true．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管他们的学校可能并不现代化，但在家附近建一所学校的梦想已经实现了。

sense_info_list.zh: (come from)来自; 产自; 由于

examination_example.sentence: One of my classmates <highlight>comes</highlight> from a tribe (部落) that lived in the west of our country.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我的一个同学来自我国西部的一个部落。

examination_example.sentence: The growth mainly <highlight>came</highlight> from China's forest protection programs, NASA said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国宇航局表示，这一增长主要来自中国的森林保护项目。

examination_example.sentence: Most of the eggs we eat <highlight>come</highlight> from hens.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们吃的大多数鸡蛋都产自母鸡。

examination_example.sentence: After <highlight>coming</highlight> out of the ground, it breaks out of its old shell.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从地里长出来之后，它破壳而出。

examination_example.sentence: He tried to ask, but words didn't <highlight>come</highlight> out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他想问，但是话没有说出口。

examination_example.sentence: Their leaves grow on the top and flowers seldom <highlight>come</highlight> out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们的叶子长在顶端,很少开花。

sense_info_list.zh: (come up with)提出; 想出; 拿出

examination_example.sentence: The Marine Conservation Society (MCS) asked local schoolchildren to <highlight>come</highlight> up with suggestions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 海洋保护协会（MCS）要求当地学生提出建议。

examination_example.sentence: Just then, Cao Chong <highlight>came</highlight> up with a great idea.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 就在那时，曹冲提出了一个好办法。

examination_example.sentence: Being creative means <highlight>coming</highlight> up with new ideas and having creative imagination.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有创造力意味着提出新的想法和拥有创造性的想象力。

examination_example.sentence: The next morning, as I was looking listlessly over the papers at breakfast, I <highlight>came</highlight> across this paragraph.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 第二天早上，当我早餐时无精打采地看着报纸，偶然发现了这一段。
